<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Development Associate</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Development Associate<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Mary Schrock<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full-time, Exempt
</p>

<p>PACER&rsquo;s development team  works with volunteers, sponsors, community representatives and internal staff  to raise funds and promote PACER events. This positions interacts with the team  in all aspects of the department, which is a collegial and energetic  environment.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ol>
	<li>Coordinate corporate sponsor committee for annual benefit. Organize meetings, communicate directly with business and corporate executives and managers, manage database and create solicitation materials.</li>
	<li>Coordinate ongoing business partnerships in the community; including logistics for communications and meetings. </li>
	<li>Assist with creating marketing ideas and new partnership opportunities.</li>
	<li>Conduct grant research and write grants for PACER&rsquo;s projects.</li>
	<li>Assist with the developing content for department&rsquo;s donor newsletter </li>
	<li>Coordinate, research and draft proposals for funding.</li>
	<li>Lead the content development for the Development web presence.</li>
	<li>Manage the internet based aspects of fund raising and promotional events.</li>
	<li>Coordinate an event to raise funds via phone. Includes recruiting and training volunteers, organizing call sheets, and invoicing.</li>
	<li>Provide the project management on special projects and initiatives.</li>
	<li>Provide staff support, as needed, for new or current committees.</li>
	<li>Assist with development, promotion and coordination of special events and projects</li>
	<li>Call corporations, foundations and individuals on behalf of PACER&rsquo;s fundraising activities.</li>
	<li>Write letters, grants and other materials for PACER.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>College degree required.</li>
	<li>Experience in  coordinating events.</li>
	<li>Ability to use  discretion and diplomacy when communicating with donors and sponsors.</li>
	<li>Excellent  organizational skills, ability prioritize and meet deadlines.</li>
	<li>Knowledge  of/sensitivity to issues and current information/research related to persons  with disabilities.</li>
	<li>Excellent verbal  and written communication skills.</li>
	<li>Accuracy and  attention to detail.</li>
	<li>Ability to manage  multiple tasks on several projects.</li>
	<li>Ability to  collaborate with coworkers and coordinate projects.</li>
	<li>Ability to work  independently and participate in team planning and decision-making process.</li>
	<li>Above average  proficiency of computer software programs; primarily Microsoft Office with an  emphasis on Word, Excel and PowerPoint and also FileMaker Pro.</li>
</ul>
<p>Parents  of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
	Salary to be determined based on experience<br />
	Position  available immediately.</p>
<p>Send  resume with a letter of application to:<br />
	Marilyn  Stoutenberg | PACER Center | 8161    Normandale Blvd | Minneapolis, MN 55437</p>
<p>PACER Center is an <em>Affirmative</em> <em>Action and Equal Employment Opportunity</em> Employer. </p>
